ype\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing MethodDelegate issues**\\n\\nI’m considering that the current comma list might include a dollar sign, which could be causing Graal not to parse correctly since it accepts a comma-separated format. It could also be too long. Perhaps the ConstructorDelegate isn't tracking user changes? I wonder if we should just add MethodDelegate without modifying the constructor. \\n\\nImproving test coverage seems crucial, especially by using the actual public API instance of MethodDelegate instead of just the static version. I’ll need to look into isolating MethodDelegate in a new URLClassLoader to ensure its static initialization runs.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring dynamic class loading**\\n\\nI’m thinking about dynamic class loading, specifically loading a library class from the same JAR in a new child-first classloader. It seems this is what dynamic class loading is, but I'm questioning if it’s fundamentally unsupported under Native Image. However, the rules suggest that I should catch an Error to verify UnsupportedFeature for dynamic class loading. This might execute Class.forName in the library class when it's reloaded, which raises some interesting concerns!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method imports**\\n\\nI’m planning to add this test to MethodDelegateTest. I wonder if I should avoid the reflection API and instead use Class.forName. There are potential imports, like java.net.URL and URLClassLoader, that might be necessary. I could get the jar URL from MethodDelegate.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation(), but I'm curious if referencing MethodDelegate initializes the class. It seems like using the class literal might cause initialization, so I need to be careful with that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code robustness**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how testing under native conditions might lead to a scenario where the class literal's code source is null, which makes building a URL impossible. I wonder if we can catch RuntimeExceptions in this case. The rules indicate dynamic class loading needs to support catching errors, but if the code source is unavailable, it may not count as an Error. So, I need to ensure my approach is robust to handle these situations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering classpath construction**\\n\\nI’m thinking we could build a URL from the system property \\\"java.class.path\\\" by scanning for entries like cglib-nodep. But I'm unsure if the native property includes the original classpath. I can’t run tests myself, so I need to make a decision. Alternatively, there's the option to use `MethodDelegate.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation()`, which seems acceptable. I also wonder if the build.gradle line might be too lengthy for Checkstyle’s max line limit.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EccYxl38E4NMtorAZPsAfIF2|fc_0802ed8f142e61a40169fba8504b04819285daa0b656013a8a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MethodDelegateTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "package cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;", "newText": "package cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;"}, {"oldText": "public class MethodDelegateTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDelegateForStaticMethodWithMatchingInterfaceSignature() {", "newText": "public class MethodDelegateTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void initializesMethodDelegateInIsolatedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        CodeSource codeSource = MethodDelegate.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\n        URL libraryLocation = codeSource.getLocation();\n\n        try (URLClassLoader loader = new URLClassLoader(new URL[] {libraryLocation}, null)) {\n            Class<?> loadedClass = Class.forName(\"net.sf.cglib.reflect.MethodDelegate\", true, loader);\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass.getName()).isEqualTo(\"net.sf.cglib.reflect.MethodDelegate\");\n            assertThat(loadedClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(loader);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (findUnsupportedFeatureError(error) == null) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsDelegateForStaticMethodWithMatchingInterfaceSignature() {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1232, "output": 2943, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29263, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778100262953, "responseId": "resp_0802ed8f142e61a40169fba828695c81928a3940f9aebb8657"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_EccYxl38E4NMtorAZPsAfIF2|fc_0802ed8f142e61a40169fba8504b04819285daa0b656013a8a", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/MethodDelegateTest.java."}], "details": {"diff": "     ...\n   5  * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n   6  */\n   7 package cglib.cglib_nodep;\n   8 \n+  9 import java.net.URL;\n+ 10 import java.net.URLClassLoader;\n+ 11 import java.security.CodeSource;\n+ 12 \n   9 import net.sf.cglib.core.CodeGenerationException;\n  10 import net.sf.cglib.reflect.MethodDelegate;\n  11 import org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\n  12 import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n     ...\n  15 \n  16 public class MethodDelegateTest {\n  17 \n  18     @Test\n+ 23     void initializesMethodDelegateInIsolatedClassLoader() throws Exception {\n+ 24         CodeSource codeSource = MethodDelegate.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\n+ 25         URL libraryLocation = codeSource.getLocation();\n+ 2